![Cover](/img/articles/cover-5-ways-adaptability.jpg)

Photo by Mobile Development on Grow with Google


Adaptability is one of the most important skills we can develop today. It shapes how we respond to change, navigate uncertainty, and continue growing in fast-shifting environments.

Joining [Bangkit Academy led by Google, Tokopedia, Gojek, & Traveloka](https://grow.google/intl/id_id/bangkit/?tab=mobile-development) was an exciting journey for me. I had to adapt to a new environment, new people, and a new way of working. Here are the 5 ways I adapted: ## 1. Interacting Adaptability starts with the way we communicate and connect with others. Being adaptable means knowing how to adjust:

- your tone, - your approach, - your expectations, - and your communication style, depending on the person and situation.

Good adaptability makes collaboration smoother and prevents unnecessary conflict. ## 2. Achieving Goals can change. Targets shift. Plans evolve. Adaptable people don‚Äôt break when expectations move ‚Äî they **adjust**.

They:

- redefine what success looks like, - adjust timelines, - remain committed despite obstacles, - and stay flexible enough to change direction when needed.

This helps them stay consistent even when conditions aren‚Äôt ideal. ## 3. Learning Adaptability thrives on learning ‚Äî and not just *any* learning.

It‚Äôs about:

- learning new things, - **re-learning** what you thought you knew, - and **un-learning** old habits that no longer work.

Continuous learners adapt faster because they‚Äôre open to new perspectives. ## 4. Working The world of work is changing rapidly ‚Äî remote work, hybrid setups, automation, new tools.

Adaptable people can:

- switch between platforms, - adjust to new workflows, - embrace new responsibilities, - and stay productive in different environments.

This keeps them relevant and resilient. ## 5. Thinking Perhaps the most important form of adaptability:

**mental adaptability**.

This means having a mindset that:

- tolerates uncertainty, - accepts that change is inevitable, - reframes challenges as opportunities, - and stays curious instead of threatened by new things.

Adaptable thinkers don‚Äôt just survive change ‚Äî they grow through it. ## Closing Thoughts Adaptability isn‚Äôt a skill you master once. It‚Äôs a lifelong practice ‚Äî a mindset of flexibility, curiosity, and openness.

The more adaptable you become, the more confidently you can navigate the unpredictable world ahead.

**Stay flexible. Stay curious. Keep evolving.**

_data.text:
![Cover](/img/articles/cover-action-on-google-introduction.jpg)

Photo by Google Assistant on Google Assistant for Developers


Hi folks, in this article I want to introduce **Action on Google**. A while ago, I had the chance to share this topic in several universities. So I thought, why not write it down here so it can reach more people as well?

At this moment, not many people are familiar with this platform, even though it can reach thousands of devices ‚Äî including smart speakers, phones, cars, TVs, headphones, and more. Action on Google itself is a platform that lets you build products which extend the functionality of **Google Assistant** and deliver rich conversational experiences. ## What Is Action on Google? With Action on Google, we as developers have the opportunity to:

- create our own custom conversational experiences, - manage conversations with users, - integrate our services into Google Assistant.

Action on Google combines three main technologies:

- machine learning - speech recognition - language understanding

These make it possible to understand what the user says and respond in a natural, conversational way. ## How Does It Work? At a high level, we use the **Conversation API** and the **Actions SDK**.

![Section-2](/img/articles/section-2.jpg)

Photo by Google Assistant on Google Assistant for Developers


- The user says something to Google Assistant. - The Action receives a request that contains the spoken text as a string. - Google handles the **speech recognition** part ‚Äî converting voice to text. - The text is then parsed and processed so the system can understand the intent. - A response is generated and Google Assistant speaks it back to the user.

The key point here: you don‚Äôt have to implement speech recognition or natural language parsing from scratch ‚Äî Google takes care of that. ## Why Dialogflow? So, what tools can you use to build an Action on Google product?

A great choice is **Dialogflow**.

![Section-3](/img/articles/section-3.jpg)

Photo by Google Assistant on Google Assistant for Developers


Dialogflow is a platform that makes it much easier to build conversational experiences. It lets you create conversational interfaces on top of your products and services by providing a powerful **Natural Language Understanding (NLU)** engine.

In other words, Dialogflow helps you process and understand natural language input, so you can focus more on the logic and experience, not on low-level language processing. ## How Dialogflow Fits In Once the user is talking to your Action, they start with what Google calls a **‚Äúuser says‚Äù** phrase.

![Section-4](/img/articles/section-4.jpg)

Photo by Google Assistant on Google Assistant for Developers


For example:

*‚ÄúHelp me find a recipe for rendang.‚Äù*

When the user says this to your Action:

- Google Assistant and Dialogflow process the phrase. - Dialogflow finds the appropriate **intent** to handle it. - The phrase is processed to extract **entities** (important pieces of information). - Dialogflow calls your **webhook** with these entities and the action name. - Your webhook does whatever logic you need (e.g., search recipes) and returns a response. - The response is then spoken back to the user.

Even though the example looks simple, conversational experiences are actually quite hard to implement if you build everything from scratch. Interpreting and processing natural language requires a very robust language parser that understands all the nuances of language.

Dialogflow helps you achieve this more easily by handling NLU for you.
When you use Dialogflow, you create **agents** that can understand varied human language and translate it into structured data that your apps and services can work with. ## Closing That‚Äôs a short introduction to **Action on Google**. In the next article, I‚Äôll try my best to share a more concrete demo or hands-on example related to this topic.

**Cheers!**

![Cover](/img/articles/cover-crticical-thinking-problem-solving.jpg)

Photo by Mobile Development on Grow with Google


In today‚Äôs fast-moving environment, solving problems isn‚Äôt about having the right answers ‚Äî it's about asking the right questions. Critical thinking is the foundation of meaningful problem-solving. It helps us:

- break down complex issues, - spot hidden assumptions, - generate better options, - and act decisively when uncertainty is high.

Choosing Bangkit was a deliberate decision for me, aiming to enhance my professionalism post-graduation. Facing significant hurdles, particularly from within, has tested my resilience and critical thinking at [Bangkit Academy led by Google, Tokopedia, Gojek, & Traveloka](https://grow.google/intl/id_id/bangkit/?tab=mobile-development). ## Why Critical Thinking Matters When you rely purely on intuition or past habits, you limit your possible solutions. But when you apply critical thinking, you expand them.

- You start asking ‚ÄúWhy?‚Äù instead of accepting ‚ÄúBecause‚Äù. - You learn to challenge how things have always been done. - You open up for better alternatives. ## The Critical Thinking Process - **Clarify** ‚Äî Identify exactly what the problem is. - **Gather** ‚Äî Collect relevant data, evidence, and perspectives. - **Analyze** ‚Äî Break down the data, look for patterns, biases, and assumptions. - **Evaluate** ‚Äî Weigh your options, list pros & cons, foresee consequences. - **Decide & Act** ‚Äî Choose a path and move, then reflect on results. ## Problem-Solving in Practice When you combine critical thinking with problem-solving, you become more than reactive ‚Äî you become strategic.

- Instead of ‚Äúfixing what‚Äôs broken‚Äù, you ask ‚ÄúWhat needs to change and why?‚Äù. - Instead of ‚Äúemergency mode‚Äù, you work in ‚Äúpurpose mode‚Äù. - Instead of repeating outcomes, you create new ones. ## Closing Thoughts Great problem-solvers don‚Äôt wait for perfect clarity ‚Äî they act on clear thinking. They recognise that almost every problem is also an opportunity for growth.

If you‚Äôre ready to level-up your thinking, start today: challenge one assumption, ask one better question, and let the process guide you.

**Stay curious. Think critically. Solve smart.**

![Cover](/img/articles/cover-quiet-growth.jpg)

## The Parts No One Sees Behind every accomplishment lies a version of ourselves that most people never meet:

- the late-night doubts, - the abandoned drafts, - the trial-error cycles, - the moments we consider giving up.
But these ‚Äúunseen‚Äù elements matter. They shape our endurance, deepen our understanding, and slowly build the resilience needed to do meaningful work. No trophy or recognition can fully represent this journey ‚Äî and maybe that‚Äôs the point. ## Trusting the Slow Pace Some seasons of life feel stagnant ‚Äî as if nothing meaningful is happening. But often, these slow seasons are the ones forming our foundation.

Just like how a tree grows its roots deeper before reaching upward, we too grow inward before we grow outward. Learning to trust the process means:

- allowing ourselves to grow at our own pace, - understanding that consistency beats intensity, - appreciating the progress that isn‚Äôt visible yet. ## Progress Looks Different for Everyone There is no universal timeline for success, creativity, or fulfillment.
What takes months for one person may take years for another ‚Äî and that‚Äôs okay.
What matters is not how fast we move, but whether we keep moving.
Real growth isn‚Äôt a race. It‚Äôs a personal journey.
## Closing Thoughts Quiet growth is still growth.
The small steps still count.
The invisible progress still matters.

If you‚Äôre in a season that feels slow, uncertain, or unremarkable ‚Äî don‚Äôt be discouraged. You‚Äôre building something beneath the surface that will carry you through the chapters ahead.

**Keep going. Trust the process. The results will come in their own time.**

children.value: Unveiling The New Interface: Juragan Material‚Äôs Homepage Redesign

Juragan Material is an Indonesian B2B e-commerce platform specializing in building materials. We aim to revolutionize the construction industry through digital transformation. This case study details our UI/UX redesign process to enhance user experience and align with the new logo launch on Apr 3, 2023. The goal is to create an engaging, intuitive, and visually captivating homepage that reflects their commitment to excellence.

Juragan Material planned to launch a new logo on Apr 3, 2023. To align with the new branding, adjustments are required for the user interface (UI) on the homepage, header, and footer. The primary goal is to enhance the user experience (UX) by addressing existing issues and making the homepage more engaging and visually appealing.

We identified critical issues with Juragan's previous homepage, including low engagement and clickability awareness. To address these challenges, we embarked on a comprehensive redesign, focusing on improving the visual hierarchy and optimizing white space usage. Our user-centric approach aims to create a captivating and seamless user experience, drawing visitors deeper into Juragan's platform

We revamped Juragan Material's homepage by restructuring its information architecture for a more streamlined user experience and optimized white space. The new design combines "Register as Business" and "Register as Vendor" into one section.

In the context of Juragan Material's homepage redesign, typography plays a crucial role in conveying a sense of professionalism and clarity to the user experience. While the logo font is Poppins, the decision to use the Inter font for the website's content was deliberate.

The font's legibility ensures that vital information is easily accessible to users, fostering a seamless browsing experience. By opting for Inter, Juragan Material ensures a consistent and visually appealing presentation that aligns with their industry expertise and trustworthy reputation.

The top banner, being a crucial element of the homepage, required a redesign that captured the attention of users and conveyed Juragan's value proposition effectively. The team collaborated to create a visually compelling banner that featured striking imagery and clear, concise messaging. A balance between aesthetics and information hierarchy was maintained to avoid overwhelming the users.
What I learned from Designing for Juragan Material

This case study's main limitation is the absence of formal research and analysis. Without user research, the design decisions may not fully meet Juragan Material's audience needs. The redesign lacks data-driven insights but serves as an exercise in exploring design improvements. The case study has tight deadlines, limiting in-depth design exploration and iterations. The pressure to deliver quickly may impact thoroughness and testing.
